{"key":"processedPost-8647517","value":{"id":8647517,"first":8646829,"last":8655088,"when":1216329538,"utime":"07/18/08 12:18 AM","content":"It matters little how much water is in the PC as long as it doesn't run dry.&nbsp; If the jars are on a shelf and you're starting the run with everything at room temperature, it sounds like a load of crappy jars.&nbsp; I've probably had five jars in the last twenty years crack while in the PC, so the problem is rare indeed.&nbsp; <br /><br />Make sure you're not doing anything to cool the PC down after the cooking cycle other than simply shutting off the stove.&nbsp; If you pop the weight to let out steam, that's the problem.&nbsp; They need to heat slowly, and then cool slowly.<br />RR","title":"Re: Breaking Jars left and right - Ball Quart Jars made in china?"}}